{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DXt5PTiYPJi2T4h6J2uvYp","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 16.5: Rewrite harness-run Verification Dispatch\n     2→<!-- verification-tier: test-provable -->\n     3→\n     4→Status: verifying\n     5→\n     6→<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n     7→\n     8→## Story\n     9→\n    10→As a codeharness developer,\n    11→I want the harness-run Step 3d verification dispatch to use four-tier routing instead of binary unit-testable/black-box,\n    12→So that each verification tier gets the appropriate verification strategy (build+test, local run, Docker stack, or escalation).\n    13→\n    14→## Acceptance Criteria\n    15→\n    16→- [ ] AC1: Given harness-run Step 3d-0, when a story file is read, then the verification tier is derived by parsing ALL AC-level `<!-- verification: {tier} -->` tags and computing `maxTier()` across them — the story-level `<!-- verification-tier: -->` tag is NOT used for dispatch <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    17→- [ ] AC2: Given a story where all ACs are tagged `test-provable`, when Step 3d dispatches, then verification runs via a single subagent that builds, runs tests, and inspects code — no Docker, no running the app <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    18→- [ ] AC3: Given a story where the derived tier is `runtime-provable`, when Step 3d dispatches, then a subagent builds the artifact, runs it locally (e.g., `npm start`, `cargo run`), interacts with it, and checks behavior — no Docker stack needed <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    19→- [ ] AC4: Given a story where the derived tier is `environment-provable`, when Step 3d dispatches, then the existing full Docker verification flow runs (`codeharness stack start`, docker exec, observability checks) <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    20→- [ ] AC5: Given a story where the derived tier is `escalate`, when Step 3d dispatches, then escalated ACs are marked `[ESCALATE]` and non-escalated ACs are verified at their individual tier levels <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    21→- [ ] AC6: Given a story file with the old `<!-- verification-tier: unit-testable -->` story-level tag, when Step 3d reads it, then the story-level tag is ignored and AC-level tier derivation is used instead (backward compat: old stories still work because their AC tags are parsed) <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    22→- [ ] AC7: Given Step 3d-0 encounters ACs with legacy tags like `<!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->` or `<!-- verification: integration-required -->`, when tier derivation runs, then `LEGACY_TIER_MAP` maps them to new tiers before computing `maxTier()` <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    23→\n    24→## Tasks / Subtasks\n    25→\n    26→- [x] Task 1: Rewrite Step 3d-0 in `commands/harness-run.md` (AC: 1, 6, 7)\n    27→  - [x] 1.1: Replace the binary `<!-- verification-tier: unit-testable -->` tag check (L261-L267) with AC-level tier derivation instructions\n    28→  - [x] 1.2: Add instructions: parse all AC lines for `<!-- verification: {tier} -->` tags, map legacy values via `LEGACY_TIER_MAP`, compute `maxTier()`. Default to `test-provable` if no tags found\n    29→  - [x] 1.3: Add note: the story-level `<!-- verification-tier: -->` tag is ignored; AC-level tags are the source of truth\n    30→- [x] Task 2: Rewrite the test-provable dispatch section (AC: 2)\n    31→  - [x] 2.1: Keep the existing unit-testable subagent prompt (L272-L302) largely as-is — this IS the test-provable path. Update the heading/label from \"Unit-testable verification\" to \"test-provable verification\"\n    32→  - [x] 2.2: Update the subagent prompt to reference \"test-provable tier\" instead of \"unit-testable tier\"\n    33→- [x] Task 3: Add runtime-provable dispatch section (AC: 3)\n    34→  - [x] 3.1: Add a new subagent prompt block for `runtime-provable`. Build the project, then run it. Try `getRunCommand()` from StackProvider if available; otherwise fall back to common commands (`npm start`, `cargo run`, `python -m app`)\n    35→  - [x] 3.2: Subagent instructions: start the app, interact (CLI flags, HTTP to localhost), check output/behavior, kill process, generate proof document\n    36→  - [x] 3.3: No Docker stack. No `codeharness stack start`. The app runs locally.\n    37→- [x] Task 4: Keep environment-provable dispatch section (AC: 4)\n    38→  - [x] 4.1: Relabel the existing \"Black-box verification (default, no tag)\" section as \"environment-provable verification\"\n    39→  - [x] 4.2: No behavioral changes — the Docker flow (3d-i through 3d-viii) stays as-is\n    40→- [x] Task 5: Add escalate dispatch section (AC: 5)\n    41→  - [x] 5.1: Add a new section for `escalate` tier. For each AC in the story, check individual AC tier. Mark `escalate`-tier ACs as `[ESCALATE]`. For non-escalated ACs, dispatch verification at their individual tier level\n    42→  - [x] 5.2: If all non-escalated ACs pass, story is done with escalation notes\n    43→- [x] Task 6: Update Step 3a create-story prompt reference (AC: 1)\n    44→  - [x] 6.1: In Step 3a (L152-L170), update the AC tagging instruction from `cli-verifiable`/`integration-required` to the four new tier names with decision criteria. (Note: this is Task 6 in the tech spec but is scoped to this story because the dispatch depends on correctly tagged ACs)\n    45→\n    46→## Dev Notes\n    47→\n    48→This story modifies a single file: `commands/harness-run.md`. It's a prompt-engineering rewrite — no TypeScript code changes, no test changes, no build changes.\n    49→\n    50→### Key Constraints"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c452ddd6-f9a0-4cb1-9871-4264c6441698","uuid":"6f9fe18b-1c11-43e3-bd0d-c562c537c860","timestamp":"2026-03-27T12:27:38.602Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/16-5-rewrite-harness-run-verification-dispatch.md","content":"# Story 16.5: Rewrite harness-run Verification Dispatch\n<!-- verification-tier: test-provable -->\n\nStatus: verifying\n\n<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n\n## Story\n\nAs a codeharness developer,\nI want the harness-run Step 3d verification dispatch to use four-tier routing instead of binary unit-testable/black-box,\nSo that each verification tier gets the appropriate verification strategy (build+test, local run, Docker stack, or escalation).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC1: Given harness-run Step 3d-0, when a story file is read, then the verification tier is derived by parsing ALL AC-level `<!-- verification: {tier} -->` tags and computing `maxTier()` across them — the story-level `<!-- verification-tier: -->` tag is NOT used for dispatch <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n- [ ] AC2: Given a story where all ACs are tagged `test-provable`, when Step 3d dispatches, then verification runs via a single subagent that builds, runs tests, and inspects code — no Docker, no running the app <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n- [ ] AC3: Given a story where the derived tier is `runtime-provable`, when Step 3d dispatches, then a subagent builds the artifact, runs it locally (e.g., `npm start`, `cargo run`), interacts with it, and checks behavior — no Docker stack needed <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n- [ ] AC4: Given a story where the derived tier is `environment-provable`, when Step 3d dispatches, then the existing full Docker verification flow runs (`codeharness stack start`, docker exec, observability checks) <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n- [ ] AC5: Given a story where the derived tier is `escalate`, when Step 3d dispatches, then escalated ACs are marked `[ESCALATE]` and non-escalated ACs are verified at their individual tier levels <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n- [ ] AC6: Given a story file with the old `<!-- verification-tier: unit-testable -->` story-level tag, when Step 3d reads it, then the story-level tag is ignored and AC-level tier derivation is used instead (backward compat: old stories still work because their AC tags are parsed) <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n- [ ] AC7: Given Step 3d-0 encounters ACs with legacy tags like `<!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->` or `<!-- verification: integration-required -->`, when tier derivation runs, then `LEGACY_TIER_MAP` maps them to new tiers before computing `maxTier()` <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n## Tasks / Subtasks\n\n- [x] Task 1: Rewrite Step 3d-0 in `commands/harness-run.md` (AC: 1, 6, 7)\n  - [x] 1.1: Replace the binary `<!-- verification-tier: unit-testable -->` tag check (L261-L267) with AC-level tier derivation instructions\n  - [x] 1.2: Add instructions: parse all AC lines for `<!-- verification: {tier} -->` tags, map legacy values via `LEGACY_TIER_MAP`, compute `maxTier()`. Default to `test-provable` if no tags found\n  - [x] 1.3: Add note: the story-level `<!-- verification-tier: -->` tag is ignored; AC-level tags are the source of truth\n- [x] Task 2: Rewrite the test-provable dispatch section (AC: 2)\n  - [x] 2.1: Keep the existing unit-testable subagent prompt (L272-L302) largely as-is — this IS the test-provable path. Update the heading/label from \"Unit-testable verification\" to \"test-provable verification\"\n  - [x] 2.2: Update the subagent prompt to reference \"test-provable tier\" instead of \"unit-testable tier\"\n- [x] Task 3: Add runtime-provable dispatch section (AC: 3)\n  - [x] 3.1: Add a new subagent prompt block for `runtime-provable`. Build the project, then run it. Try `getRunCommand()` from StackProvider if available; otherwise fall back to common commands (`npm start`, `cargo run`, `python -m app`)\n  - [x] 3.2: Subagent instructions: start the app, interact (CLI flags, HTTP to localhost), check output/behavior, kill process, generate proof document\n  - [x] 3.3: No Docker stack. No `codeharness stack start`. The app runs locally.\n- [x] Task 4: Keep environment-provable dispatch section (AC: 4)\n  - [x] 4.1: Relabel the existing \"Black-box verification (default, no tag)\" section as \"environment-provable verification\"\n  - [x] 4.2: No behavioral changes — the Docker flow (3d-i through 3d-viii) stays as-is\n- [x] Task 5: Add escalate dispatch section (AC: 5)\n  - [x] 5.1: Add a new section for `escalate` tier. For each AC in the story, check individual AC tier. Mark `escalate`-tier ACs as `[ESCALATE]`. For non-escalated ACs, dispatch verification at their individual tier level\n  - [x] 5.2: If all non-escalated ACs pass, story is done with escalation notes\n- [x] Task 6: Update Step 3a create-story prompt reference (AC: 1)\n  - [x] 6.1: In Step 3a (L152-L170), update the AC tagging instruction from `cli-verifiable`/`integration-required` to the four new tier names with decision criteria. (Note: this is Task 6 in the tech spec but is scoped to this story because the dispatch depends on correctly tagged ACs)\n\n## Dev Notes\n\nThis story modifies a single file: `commands/harness-run.md`. It's a prompt-engineering rewrite — no TypeScript code changes, no test changes, no build changes.\n\n### Key Constraints","numLines":50,"startLine":1,"totalLines":130}}}
